An cafke jami'an 'yan sandan Kenya bayan harbe-harben da aka yi a Garissa
An cafke wasu ‘yan sanda biyu a Kenya dangane da harbe-harben da ya yi sanadin mutuwar mutane biyu.
Harbe-harben ya faru ne a kasuwar Soko Ng'ombe da ke gabashin karamar hukumar Garissa a ranar Asabar, yayin zanga-zangar adawa da kame wani mutum da ake zargi da kisan kai.
An bayyana sunayen mutanen biyu da Aden Abdi Madoobe da Muhiyadin Adow Shibin.
Hukumar ‘yan sanda a kasar Kenya ta fara bincike game da harbe-harben.
Zai kunshi "binciken kwakwaf" na bindigogin jami'an.
Dan majalisa mai wakiltar Garissa, Aden Ducaale ya kira mutuwar a matsayin "mummunan" kuma ya yi Allah wadai da "ta'addancin 'yan sanda" a cikin wata sanarwa da ya wallafa a Facebook.
Masu fafutuka sun nuna damuwa game da 'yan sanda yayin annobar.
A cewar Amnesty International, jami'an Kenya sun kashe mutane 21 tun a watan Maris saboda kin bin matakan rigakafin cutar Coronavirus kamar dokar hana fita da sanya fuska.
A farkon wannan watan ne 'yan sanda a Nairobi babban birnin kasar suka harba hayaki mai sa hawaye kuma suka kame masu zanga-zangar da dama wadanda ke halartar tattakin na Saba Saba na shekara-shekara - zanga-zangar da aka fara shekaru 30 da suka gabata kan adawa da mulkin kama-karya na Shugaba na lokacin Daniel arap Moi.
Masu aiko da rahotanni sun ce bikin na bana an ba shi karin kuzari saboda fushin da 'yan sanda suka yi a lokacin da aka kulle Covid-19.
Shivraj Singh Chouhan Akan Gwada Gaskiya
Babban Ministan Madhya Pradesh Shivraj Singh Chouhan, wanda a ranar Asabar ya tabbatar da cewa ya yi gwajin cutar ta COVID-19, ya wallafa a shafinsa na lahadi da safiyar Lahadi cewa yana "lafiya" kuma ya ba da yabo ga ma'aikatan gaba-gaba a yakin da ake yi da kwayar cutar ta coronavirus.
Babban Ministan har ila yau ya maimaita gargadin nasa daga jiya, lokacin da ya bukaci mutane da su bi ka’idoji, kamar nisantar zamantakewa da amfani da abin rufe fuska.
"Ina cikin koshin lafiya, abokaina. Sadaukarwar mayaka kwaronavirus, wadanda suka sadaukar da rayukansu, abin a yaba ne. Ina jinjina wa dukkan mayaka masu kwarorona na jihar," Mista Chouhan ya wallafa a shafinsa na Tweita daga asibitin Chirayu na Bhopal, inda aka kwantar da shi a jiya.
"Kiyaye nisan mita biyu, wanke hannuwanku akai-akai kuma sanya abin rufe fuska - wadannan su ne manyan makamai da muke da su don kauce wa kwayar ta corona. Ina kira ga dukkan mutane - ku yi amfani da wadannan makamai don kanku da masoyanku," in ji shi.
Mista Chouhan ya kara da cewa "Dukkanku ku yi hankali, ku zauna lafiya da koshin lafiya. Abin da nake rokon Allah ke nan."
A ranar Asabar Mr Chouhan ya wallafa a shafinsa na Tweeter cewa ya yi gwajin kwayar cutar duk da kokarin da ya yi na kauce wa kamuwa da cutar kuma ya yi gargadin cewa "dan rashin kulawa ne kawai ke gayyatar kwayar ta kwayar cutar.
A sakon da ya wallafa a safiyar yau Mista Chouhan ya ce duk da barazanar kamuwa da cutar "babu bukatar a ji tsoro" kuma ya bukaci wadanda ke nuna alamun da su gwada kansu.
"Idan kun kamu da cutar, to babu bukatar ku ji tsoro. Kada ku ɓoye alamun cutar amma ku gaya wa likitoci nan da nan, don haka za a iya fara jinya. Maganin da ya dace zai ba ku lafiya," in ji shi.
Madhya Pradesh tana da cutar kusan 27,000 COVID-19, wanda sama da 7,600 ke aiki kuma 799 sun mutu masu nasaba da kwayar.
Indiya ta sami karuwar karuwa a cikin shari'ar COVID-19 a cikin makonnin da suka gabata, tare da gano sabbin mutane sama da 45,000 a kowace rana tun daga ranar 23 ga Yulin.
